(396, 1, '2017-12-22 19:39:55', '2017-12-22 18:39:55', '<h1 class=\"title-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">CSUDH Innovation Incubator</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-369 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/logo-incubator.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"249\" height=\"119\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5 class=\"title-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The new Innovation Incubator at CSUDH is an Incubator/Accelerator for startups and existing businesses.</strong></h5>\r\n<p class=\"title-2\" style=\"text-align: left;\">The Incubator  provides practitioner based entrepreneurial education that “teaches them what they do not know” about business and entrepreneurship. The mentor-focused Innovation Incubator’s mission is to “empower social entrepreneurs\" by serving as a catalyst and economic engine for the South Bay region and beyond.\"</p>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-366 aligncenter\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Photo-2.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<h5>Methodologies</h5>\r\nWe use <strong><em>three</em></strong> pillars for our Innovation Incubator:\r\n\r\nOur first pillar is <strong>Coaching. </strong> We will <strong>coach</strong> our clients by providing both Primary Mentors and Secondary Specialist mentors to provide one-on-one advisement to help our clients grow their businesses<strong>. ALL clients must be coachable</strong>, otherwise they will be told that <em>‘we cannot help them”</em> as part of our exit interview.  The Mentors and Clients will be paired by the Selection Committee.  Hopefully these personal relationships will be very successful and become known as our secret sauce to our Innovation Incubator program.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur second pillar is <strong>Collaboration. </strong> We will foster <strong>collaboration</strong> during monthly Client Collaboration (Best Practices) meetings.  Clients will share their success and failures for the past 30 days and their plan and goals for the next 30 days during this meeting.  Occasionally, guest speakers will also participate periodically to offer educational tips.  Collaboration of like-minded entrepreneurs is oftentimes the most rewarding of the entire incubator experience. We will foster that entrepreneurship is a team sport. <strong>Our third pillar</strong> is Cultivation. We will cultivate our clients using the power of practical education. We will essentially teach them what they do not know during our on-going practitioner based educational certificate programs. We believe that entrepreneurship can be taught.\r\n\r\n<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14.4px; vertical-align: baseline; background: #ffffff; color: #1d1d1d; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"> </em>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-370\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/photo-3.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Tudigo</h1>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/logo-tudigo.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"492\" height=\"295\" />\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Be a part of something smaller</b><b> : </b><b>Invest LOCAL</b></h5>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Tudigo is a local crowdfunding platform that connects local businesses with local investors with Funding , Local visibility , Business community creation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">Fliping up the system to save Made in local America</h5>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In recent years, research by American Express Small Business Saturday has shown that over 90% of Americans value the small businesses in their community. That’s because small businesses are the lifeblood of any community. These are your butcher, your baker, your neighbor. When you go to Walmart, you don’t shake hands with the CEO. You don’t call your grocery bagger by name. You don’t ask the cashier about her kids. You don’t know any of them.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">But for Susan, the local restaurant owner, you’re Jaclyn, you’re Gary, you’re Bob, her neighbor. You live down the street. Your kids go to school together. Susan has a personal interest in you enjoying your meal because she cares about you as a person, not just a figure. Now, does that sound like a place that you want to live in?</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-382\" src=\"http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/nick-karvounis-451562.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"746\" height=\"497\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">If over ninety percent of Americans want to support their local small businesses, how do we explain that by the second year of a small business’s life, 34% have gone out of business. By year 5, 50%. Think about it. Arguably the most creative, entrepreneurial country in the world, with the second largest economy, and half of all small businesses fail. Why is that?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Well, 8 out of 10 businesses that fail do so because of cash flow problems. In fact, 77% of small businesses rely on personal savings to finance their companies, at least in the early stages. This means, folks, that people aren’t getting their capital from the banks, making it a ripe market indeed for platforms like Tudigo. New regulations like the JOBS Act are opening up the US market to equity crowdfunding.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">Tudigo, the pionner of local crowdfunding since 2013</h5>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Born in France in 2013 and after successfully close to a thousand businesses with crowdfunding success rates of 74% (Yes that\'s 40% higher that what you would achieve on Kickstarter or Indiegogo), Tudigo is finally expanding to the US</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The possibilities of the Tudigo platform are multiple.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The first option open to entrepreneurs is <strong>reward-based crowdfunding,</strong> used to raise between $1,000 and $150,000.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Moving up the food chain, we have <strong>equity-based crowdfunding,</strong> used primarily to raise between $30,000 and $1 million. Within equity crowdfunding, the client may choose to issue shares to his or her investors, provide royalties to his or her investors, or accept loans, instead of traditional investments, from clients.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Finally, Tudigo offers the <strong>White Label Solution.</strong> Through this solution, Tudigo provides a crowdfunding platform for the client, through which the client can accept crowdfunding projects by small business owners. This gives the client a way to advertise their name and to gain notoriety as an entity that cares about the small business community.</p>', 'Behind the initiative', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-22 19:39:55', '2017-12-22 18:39:55', '', 220, 'http://nakayobenin.com/tudigo/2017/12/22/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
